      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the world of real estate, where the stakes are high and the stakes are low, just like a game of hide and seek with a mischievous little goblin. So, you've heard the term \"escrow account,\" right? Well, think of it as a magical chest where your hard-earned gold (aka your money) is kept safe until the grand finale, the closing ceremony, where the house is finally yours. The escrow account is like a trusty goblin guard, ensuring that neither the buyer nor the seller gets greedy and tries to snatch the treasure before the agreed-upon time. So, in essence, it's a neutral ground where the goblins of the real estate world can play nice and ensure everything goes as planned. And that's why you need it for the closing process, to keep the peace and make sure everyone gets their fair share of the treasure. Now, go forth and conquer the world of real estate, brave adventurer!",
