    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, my apologies, noble inquirer. Let us venture back to the realm of mortals and shed some light on the matter with less goblin lore and more straightforward explanation. An escrow account, in the context of your condo purchase in Toronto, is a financial arrangement where a third party holds and regulates the payment of the funds required for two parties involved in a given transaction. It helps make transactions more secure by keeping the payment in a secure escrow account which is only released when all of the terms of an agreement are met as overseen by the escrow company.\n\nIn the case of your condo purchase, here's how it works: When you decide to buy a condo, you and the seller agree on a price. You then deposit the agreed-upon amount into the escrow account. This account is managed by a neutral third party, often an escrow company or a title company, who ensures that the funds are secure and that both you and the seller are meeting your obligations. The funds in the escrow account are released to the seller once all the conditions of the sale are met, such as the successful completion of a home inspection, the signing of the sale agreement, and the transfer of the property title.\n\nThe escrow company acts as the guardian of the funds",
      "source": "target",
